  <user-story>
    <as-a>user (viewer or maker)</as-a>
    <i-want>to view all my notifications in an activity feed</i-want>
    <so-that>I can catch up on missed events and access notification details</so-that>
  </user-story>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion id="ac1">Activity feed displays all notifications in reverse chronological order with read/unread visual distinction (bold text, blue indicator).</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac2">**PERFORMANCE CRITICAL**: Feed loads first 50 notifications within 500ms with infinite scroll pagination for older notifications.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac3">Notification tiles show icon, title, body preview, timestamp, and tap to view full details or navigate to related content.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac4">Unread badge count displayed on tab bar icon, updating in real-time when new notifications arrive.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac5">"Mark all as read" action available in activity feed header, updating all unread notifications in single operation.</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac6">Individual notification tap marks as read, updates badge count, and navigates to relevant screen (story, auction, order).</criterion>
    <criterion id="ac7">**ACCESSIBILITY**: Activity feed meets WCAG 2.1 AA with semantic labels, proper focus order, and screen reader announcements for new notifications.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
